P(0<Y<0.25\;|\;X=0.5)
f(x,y)=6(1-x)\;\; 0\leq y \leq x \leq 1
P(0<Y<0.25\;|\;X=0.5)=\dfrac{f(x,y)}{f_X(x)}
f_X(x)=\int_0^x6(1-x)\;dy=6x(1-x)
\dfrac{6(1-x)}{6x(1-x)}=2
\int_0^{0.25}2\;dy=0.5
X
   f_X(x) = \int_0^x 6(1-x) dy = 6x(1 - x), \ \ 0 < x < 1, 
   f_{Y\mid X}(y \mid x) = \frac{f(x,y)}{f_X(x)} = \frac{6(1-x)\chi\{ y < x \}}{6x(1-x)} = \frac{\chi\{ y < x \}}{x}. 
   P[0 < Y < 0.25 \mid X = 0.5] = \int_0^{0.25} f_{Y\mid X}(y \mid 0.5) dy = \int_0^{0.25} \frac{1}{ 0.5} dy = \frac{1}{2}. 
